  "description": "VMware vCenter / ESXi monitoring template for the NetXMS agent 'vcenter' extension. Collects VM, datastore and ESXi host CPU/memory utilization and datastore usage via agent metrics VMware.*, with instance discovery from the agent lists VMware.VMList / VMware.DatastoreList / VMware.HostList. The instance key is the managed-object ID (MOID); an instance filter resolves the human-readable name (VMware.*.Name) for display as {instance-name}.",
  "events": [],
  "templates": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "guid": "8d726a12-1f93-48e9-8609-196737ce0560",
      "name": "VMware vCenter / ESXi Monitoring",
      "comments": "Monitors a VMware vCenter (or standalone ESXi) environment through the NetXMS agent 'vcenter' extension (contrib/extensions/vcenter-python).\n\nThe extension polls vCenter on its own timer and serves all data from an in-memory cache, so DCI polling never hits vCenter directly.\n\nInstance discovery uses the agent lists VMware.VMList, VMware.DatastoreList and VMware.HostList. The instance key is the managed-object ID (MOID), which is stable across renames. Each DCI carries an instance filter that resolves the human-readable name via the VMware.{VM,Datastore,Host}.Name metric and exposes it as {instance-name}, falling back to the MOID if the name cannot be read. The full inventory is also available in the VMware.VMs / VMware.Datastores / VMware.Hosts tables.\n\nBind this template to the node whose agent runs the vcenter extension.\n\nDefault thresholds:\n  VM/Host CPU usage:     warning >= 80%, critical >= 90-95%\n  VM/Host memory usage:  warning >= 85%, critical >= 95%\n  Datastore usage:       warning >= 85%, critical >= 95%",
      "path": [
        "VMware"
      ],
      "dataCollection": {
        "dcis": [
          {
            "id": 3,
            "guid": "49303a78-26f8-4d8e-99d2-95a314dd9b85",
